A leader Mmusi Maimane is expected to address the media on Wednesday. The DA's Federal Executive met today to discuss the immediate future of outgoing Johannesburg Mayor Herman Mashaba. JOHANNESBURG - DA leader Mmusi Maimane is expected to announce his resignation on Wednesday afternoon following the party's Federal Executive meeting. The DA's Federal Executive met on Wednesday morning to discuss the immediate future of outgoing Johannesburg Mayor Herman Mashaba. READ: Zille: I've always been friends with Mashaba Mashaba resigned on Monday after Helen Zille was appointed Federal Council Chair this past weekend. Zille takes over from James Self who has vacated the office.